The paper deals with the design of algorithms for solving semidefinite programs, which is a topic in optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The focus is on parallel algorithms, which suggests a connection to distributed computing and parallel processing (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of matrix algebra and inequalities, which are topics in linear algebra and mathematical analysis (cs.IT). The use of optimization techniques and the comparison to LP solvers suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
